<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <link href="/css/output.css" rel="stylesheet" />
    <title>Nexus - Home Page</title>
  </head>
  <body class="bg-yellow-400 p-0 m-0 font-JetBrains">
    <style>
      #next-step-section {
        margin-top: 20px;
        padding: 15px;
        background: #111;
        border: 1px solid #ffcc00;
        border-radius: 8px;
        color: white;
      }

      #process-btn {
        background: #ffcc00;
        padding: 10px 16px;
        border-radius: 6px;
        border: none;
        cursor: pointer;
        font-weight: bold;
      }
    </style>
    <div class="px-2 py-4 flex flex-col text-center gap-4 mx-auto">
      <div><h1 class="text-4xl">Welcome to Nexus</h1></div>
      <div class="mx-auto px-8 w-1/2 flex flex-col gap-4">
        <p>
          <b>Nexus</b> is a<b
            ><u> Node.js-powered distributed job processing system</u></b
          >
          optimized for high-volume image and video compression pipelines. It
          uses <b>Multer</b> for upload ingestion, <b>Cloudinary</b> for raw
          media storage, <b>BullMQ</b> for queue orchestration, <b>Redis</b>>
          for fast job dispatching, and <b><u>FFmpeg-based workers</u></b> for
          compute-intensive processing.
        </p>
        <img src="/assets/nexus-blueprint.png" class="rounded-2xl" />
        <p>
          A persistent NoSQL layer (<b>MongoDB</b>) stores job metadata,
          status,7 logs, and idempotency keys, ensuring reliable execution even
          across worker restarts or failures. Real-time job tracking is
          delivered through Server-Sent Events, reducing client-side polling
          overhead and enabling a seamless user experience.
        </p>

        <p
          class="border-dashed border-2 rounded-sm p-4 bg-black text-yellow-400"
        >
          Nexus is built with scalability in mind—supporting containerized
          deployments, horizontal worker scaling, and distributed processing
          across multiple nodes.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="px-2 py-4 mx-auto w-1/2">
      <h1 class="text-4xl text-center"><u>Upload images for compression</u></h1>
      <form
        id="form"
        method="POST"
        enctype="multipart/form-data"
        class="border-dashed border-2 rounded-sm p-4 bg-black text-yellow-400 mt-4 flex flex-col"
      >
        <div class="flex flex-col">
          <label for="files" class="border-2 cursor-pointer w-fit mx-auto px-4 py-2 rounded-lg"
            >Add files</label
          >
          <input
            id="files"
            name="files"
            type="file"
            accept="image/png, image/gif, image/jpeg"
            multiple
            style="opacity: 0;"
            onchange="loadFile(event)"
            
          />
        </div>
        <div id="preview-img" class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 mt-4 px-4 py-2"></div>
        <button
          class="cursor-pointer bg-yellow-400 text-black whitespace-nowrap transition-all duration-300 mx-auto mt-4 rounded-md px-4 py-2 text-lg"
          type="submit" id="btn-submit"
        >
          Upload
        </button>
     
      <div id="next-step-section" class=" border-dashed border-2 text-center" style="display: none">
        <h3>Uploads completed ✔</h3>
        <p>Your files are now ready to send to Nexus for processing.</p>
        <button id="process-btn">Start Processing</button>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="toast" class="hidden fixed top-4 right-4 bg-black text-yellow-400 px-4 py-2 rounded-md shadow-lg"></div>

    <script src="/js/script.js"></script>

  
  </body>
</html>
